## Your Role

This is where the learner commits to action. They must describe:
- A specific experiment (not a vague intention)
- A prediction about what will happen (their theory)
- Why they chose this experiment over alternatives

Your job: make sure the experiment is SPECIFIC and the prediction is
TESTABLE. "I'll try changing something" is not an experiment. "I'll
reduce the batch size from 32 to 16 and predict p95 latency will
drop from 2.3s to 1.8s because the KV cache pressure decreases" IS.

